ce9c8cae5ed42d58dc23650dcdc665fe.description: NOTICE OF EX PARTE COMMUNICATION As an interested party in the net metering proceeding at the California Public Utilities Commission, R.20-08-020, CADEM Assembly Delegate (AD10) Lee Miller gives notice of the attached ex parte communication on behalf of herself and the other organizations listed on the communication. Today, on October 4, 2023, CADEM Assembly Delegate (AD10) Lee Miller sent the attached resolutions from local California Democratic Party organizations to all five Commissioners, as well as Kerry Fleisher in the Office of President Alice Reynolds, Cheryl Wynn and Jack Chang in the Office of Commissioner Genevieve Shiroma, Karin Sung, Maryam Mozafari, and Adam Buchholz in the Office of Commissioner Darcie Houck, Suzanne Casazza and Maria Sotero in the Office of Commissioner John Reynolds, and Kourtney Vaccaro and Simi Rose George in the Office of Commissioner Karen Douglas. The resolutions were also sent to staff of Governor Gavin Newsom. The resolutions express opposition to the proposed decision that would effectively deny renters living in multifamily homes, schools and farms the ability to directly lower their utility bills through rooftop solar and battery storage. The resolutions call for the CPUC to allow on-site netting for all utility customers with multiple meters, with no exceptions.

188bff9d180563ffb90c4b20df9a5c59.description: NOTTICE OF EX PARTE COMMUNICATION Pursuant to Rule 8.4 of the Rules of Practice and Procedure of the California Public Utilities Commission (CPUC), as an interested party in the net metering proceeding at the CPUC, R.20-08-020, Prologis gives notice of an ex parte communication. On September 5, 2023, the following individuals met via video conference with Kerry Fleisher, Chief Policy Advisor, and Simi George, Energy Advisor, to CPUC President Alice Busching Reynolds.  -Scott Peattie, Prologis, VP, Commercial and Industrial Energy Solutions-Alexis Moch, Prologis, Director, Government Affairs -Faith Conley, Weidman Group At the meeting, participants discussed the following points: The proposed VNEM and NEMA tariffs do not come close to enabling cost-effective projects, including with energy storage. Both tariffs are important. Standalone multi-tenant buildings are a good fit for VNEM, whereas clusters of buildings are a better fit for NEMA. These tariffs are important for enabling solar on commercial warehouses in urban areas, where local distribution is lacking. The meeting was requested by Mr. Peattie. It started at 1:30 pm and lasted 30 minutes. No materials were presented.

292a204f9d7a69e96ca6e76283321c88.description: SAN DIEGO COMMUNITY POWERS NOTICE OF EX PARTE COMMUNICATION Pursuant to Rule 8.4 of the Rules of Practice and Procedure of the California Public Utilities Commission (Commission or CPUC), San Diego Community Power (SDCP) hereby provides notice of the following ex parte meeting. Kerry Fleisher, Chief Policy Advisor to President Alice Busching Reynolds met with SDCP on Thursday, October 26, 2023, from 11:30 a.m. to 12:00 p.m. by phone/video conference. Aisha Cervantes-Cissna, Senior Policy Manager, SDCP; Lucas Utouh, Director of Data Analytics and Account Services, SDCP; Leslie Brown, Director of Account Services, Peninsula Clean Energy; and Steven Halligan, Regulatory and Legislative Manager for Orange County Power Authority participated on behalf of SDCP in the meeting.

f9847e7b00fcfea85e8b3e1cf6d0fe7c.description: ADVANCE NOTICE OF EX PARTE COMMUNICATION Pursuant to Rule 8.2 of the Rules of Practice and Procedure of the California Public Utilities Commission (Commission), the California Solar & Storage Association (CALSSA) hereby gives advance notice of an ex parte communication relevant to Commission Rulemaking 20-08-020. On October 26, 2023, Kerry Fleisher of the Office of President Alice Reynolds will meet via Webex with Patrick Sterns and Bronte Payne of Sunpower, Dover Janis and Allie Detrio of Ivy Energy, Sumeet Sinha and Pete Mendonez of PearlX Infrastructure, and Brad Heavner of CALSSA. The meeting is scheduled to begin at 3:00 pm. The meeting will include discussion of billing methodology under proposed changes to virtual net metering and meter aggregation.

d733ccab5ca3988811383f9a134d963c.description: NOTICE OF EX PARTE COMMUNICATION OF THE CALIFORNIA ENERGY STORAGE ALLIANCE Pursuant to Rule 8.4 of the California Public Utilities Commission Rules of Practice and Procedure, the California Energy Storage Association (CESA) provides notice of the attached ex parte communication.  On October 25, 2023, CESA sent the attached letter to all five Commissioners, as well as Kerry Fleisher in President Reynolds office, Cheryl Wynn in Commissioner Shiromas office, Karin Sung, Maryam Mozafari and Adam Buchholz in Commissioner Houcks office, Suzanne Casazza and Maria Sotero in Commissioner Reynolds office, and Kourtney Vaccaro and Simi Rose George in Commissioner Douglas office. The letter urges the Commission to adopt modify the Proposed Decision currently on the Nov. 2 agenda in this docket in a manner that allows for property-wide netting for Virtual Net Metering and Net Metering Aggregation.

2322f3f51dd6e4b531e62644b9f5cf4e.description: THREE-DAY ADVANCE NOTICE OF EX PARTE MEETING OF THE PUBLIC ADVOCATES OFFICE In accordance with Rule 8.2(c)(2)(B) of the California Public Utilities Commission’s (Commission) Rules of Practice and Procedure, the Public Advocates  Office at the California Public Utilities Commission (Cal Advocates hereby provides notice that it has been granted an ex parte meeting in proceedings Rulemaking  (R.) 20-08-020 (Revisiting Net Energy Metering Tariffs) to discuss priorities for developing a NEM successor tariff with representatives from the office of Commissioner Genevieve Shiroma.  Cal Advocates’ intention is to discuss the NEM successor tariff, but due to the potential for overlap in the discussion with the related proceedings, R.20-05-012 (Policies, Procedures and Rules for the Self Generation Incentive Program), and R.22-07-005 (Advancing Demand Flexibility Through Electric Rates), Cal Advocates is simultaneously serving a copy of this notice on the service lists for these related proceedings in an abundance of caution. The meeting will take place via Webex/teleconference call at 2:30 PM PST on December 6, 2022.   Attending the meeting for Commissioner Shiroma’s Office will be: Andrew Dugowson, Energy and Transportation Advisor; Joanna Perez-Green, Energy and Communications Advisor. Attending the meeting for the Cal Advocates will be: Michael Campbell, Branch Manager; Shelly Lyser, Program and Project Supervisor; Cindy Li, Program and Project Supervisor; Nathan Chau, Public Utilities Regulatory Analyst; Justin Ong, Public Utilities Regulatory Analyst; Wayne A. Parker, Attorney The meeting will last approximately 30 minutes.
